  "conclusions": {
    "copperfield_usage_cliff": "Both detect at day 30 with 11 days lead. Shallow detects health_yellow + low_seat_penetration; deep detects health_usage_divergence (computed from actual login data showing the cliff in user activity). Deep computes the divergence from real data rather than pre-set fixtures.",
    "harborview_renewal_risk": "Both detect at day 30 with 15 days lead time before renewal. Shallow path sees health_red (from book simulator direct band change), deep path sees health_yellow (computed from underlying data streams). Both provide adequate early warning.",
    "overall": "Deep path detects 30 accounts with risks vs 16 in shallow (87.5% more). Deep finds risks an average of 38.5 days earlier. Blue Ridge Transport improves by 150 days (shallow: day 180, deep: day 30). 14 accounts are only detected by the deep path. The deep path excels at health_usage_divergence and single_threaded_risk because it computes from actual per-user login histories rather than aggregate fixtures.",
    "pinnacle_champion_risk": "Both paths detect at day 30. Deep path computes health from actual login data (red->yellow transition) vs shallow which uses pre-set fixture (green->yellow). Deep path detects the same day but with richer signal: health is computed from login histories showing champion inactivity directly."
  },
